{"id": "82447aa31d2b2b609e1007c06a11e52c45de8bd7c42110b76233c5db33c0725a", "item_id": "5cec499585:0", "text": "To get up and rendering with Stylized Looks in Blender is very straightforward and only requires a few simple steps."}
{"id": "ed7d3aad201f4f0d26b4e6c297f905254181a8ff5a323ca588c86e96ea6ef6be", "item_id": "5cec499585:1", "text": "RenderMan Materials"}
{"id": "80adcd8416e726968666a37ef3782d5bdd737ebef2ce577b693d857af057bc7d", "item_id": "5cec499585:2", "text": "Make sure you add a light to your scene and attach a RenderMan material to your objects before rendering with Stylized Looks."}
{"id": "816b6f7e1e4f28eb5cc6897d9925be3c7eb098f72a1366760bd9a68acaa8209f", "item_id": "5cec499585:3", "text": "Right-click in the viewport and select"}
{"id": "aa9f146c3d424a8c4b32f5ba83d79579f5d0892e81b6167e459582e2c1c8e4c4", "item_id": "5cec499585:12", "text": "RenderMan"}
{"id": "a88bd40266964df79b8ed4db5a39e6481deba65637f44d4d5b94fdb21e30ca49", "item_id": "5cec499585:5", "text": "Stylized"}
{"id": "c64fb0872e9dfa5def312ae39f7bd36cf25c92470b60c42b704f2faba832cacb", "item_id": "5cec499585:6", "text": "Looks"}
{"id": "7f359436f2e7a543075082b2093fb9de4836e8791aa8b1c99dcfeb0998f7f199", "item_id": "5cec499585:7", "text": "Stylized Looks Editor"}
{"id": "615b896525006546798fef73abadd6a14e515657d9b934ac6963d2d37d02ef54", "item_id": "5cec499585:8", "text": "Enable Stylized Looks, select an object, and then select a PxrStylizedControl from Attach Stylized Pattern."}
{"id": "b5df168408698494e1c53e61573833ef5f8df32d2387e90598894063564557d2", "item_id": "5cec499585:9", "text": "Pressing OK will now create and attach the required PxrStylizedControl nodes to the PxrSurface of the robot model."}
{"id": "c8b5311f6735c78e19ba86b3cb646915da3b9bb042f25c16710135f4cb69cea3", "item_id": "5cec499585:10", "text": "The PxrStylizedControl network is required to be attached to every object in your scene and allows for individual shading control of each object."}
{"id": "f45a3c38bb900f6bffcb2c96fe348414d1f9c0f0e23689fefc63c2d5e7a3661e", "item_id": "5cec499585:11", "text": "This can also be achieved by selecting an object and"}
{"id": "81b3b65073911300398936b1f0044f39742d70f27ad1a7d0486cd4d6f1097406", "item_id": "5cec499585:14", "text": "Attach Stylized Pattern"}
{"id": "d283ef081c33967f2c80c57228ce9f4d2e9836ee4afbe1e7303455a199d48d35", "item_id": "5cec499585:15", "text": "PxrStylizedControl"}
{"id": "225c3c1f76b6a370c7998c46ab2fdafcf4d8f67bec86deed54d42c80919019ba", "item_id": "5cec499585:16", "text": "Using the RenderMan Stylized Editor, you can now begin to add in Stylized Filters to begin creating your unique Stylized Look."}
{"id": "1a60e8d42195c49641837883bd102f057aef89356ffd47e4c6e2bcb3ec3a2d34", "item_id": "5cec499585:17", "text": "In this example, we'll add in a PxrStylizedHatching Filter"}
{"id": "311022306098026f00e319d45e37adf1aa587a39570cecda0c2612a4c4028943", "item_id": "5cec499585:18", "text": "Now, fire up the IPR, and your scene will now be rendering in Stylized Looks"}
{"id": "a872a13138607468e6494469d321623544f2f686bfea1860c66879b04732e36c", "item_id": "5cec499585:19", "text": "Note:  In this example, the default settings have been tweaked in the following :"}
{"id": "4aa9868ce180102abbe3c24f4224a9f982379ccd371981b0bd6f641ff688e37b", "item_id": "5cec499585:20", "text": "a) Signal Energy From :"}
{"id": "06242946da1f878f33747adcc8c1752247a03ca72211ecf4a3b9993883974e5d", "item_id": "5cec499585:21", "text": "Albedo AOV"}
{"id": "b26640255f8897f991d1d531da7b6f050b19e0780189707a3d83c31299634801", "item_id": "5cec499585:22", "text": "b) Blending Mode :"}
{"id": "ec0fad25382b164208db5569ef38152b17f88cea3df334667db69292a6a95f5d", "item_id": "5cec499585:23", "text": "Weighted"}
{"id": "61606943494c066f52d91098bfaf48be5ba999c49eb745c2a49921a7c6b30ced", "item_id": "5cec499585:24", "text": "c) Blend Black Darkest :"}
{"id": "e8a01133b1351e5fa434167135400d1998d3daa8ce74e3dd9bb57582fa4d7b97", "item_id": "5cec499585:25", "text": "ON"}
{"id": "dc8834927e52b749f7c0ae454a432626e57492f176bfef5839bf46ebe158df12", "item_id": "5cec499585:26", "text": "d) Projection :"}
{"id": "6f5377c880f3d41fcc91bb23698945286c97ec43067a49b003b81283a331208b", "item_id": "5cec499585:28", "text": "e) Hatching Frequency :"}
{"id": "b3651eefac7726712a09619161eac077e54018c75d6c3695482d7b597d311479", "item_id": "5cec499585:29", "text": "You are now up and rendering with Stylized Looks!"}
{"id": "05447feb1d4948167a1ec8f391592287393f8de0a13ea03a54cbafde0d89a8d1", "item_id": "5cec499585:30", "text": "Your creative adventure into NPR has started and don't forget that the power of Stylized Looks comes when you begin to combine a variety of Stylized Filters together to create your own unique styles and looks."}
{"id": "ef6777086ff6f8afc2f900e348c44cac3a1beeac5d2d5ea7ff0c78d057559f81", "item_id": "5cec499585:31", "text": "Stylized Looks also ships with several fun presets to get you started.  You can find these inside the RenderMan Preset Browser"}
